Generate a infectivity profile matrix from a long format

Source: R/infectivity-profile.R
omega_matrix.Rd

This converts a long format infectivity profile to something that will work with EpiEstim. In general ggoutbreak will do the conversion internally. This is provided as a utility for examples mostly.

Usage

omega_matrix(ip = i_discrete_ip, epiestim_compat = TRUE)

Arguments

ip

long format infectivity profile - a dataframe with columns:

  • boot (anything + default(1)) - a bootstrap identifier

  • probability (proportion) - the probability of new event during this period.

  • tau (integer + complete) - the days since the index event.

Minimally grouped by: boot (and other groupings allowed).

A default value is defined.

epiestim_compat

ensure the matrix works with EpiEstim's si_from_sample method by making probability at time zero equal to zero.

Value

a matrix with 0:max(tau) rows and 1:max(boot) columns.
